      "description": "Offered is a pristine 2004 Porsche 911 Carrera 4S, a quintessential example of the widebody 996.2. This M96-powered flat-six has been fastidiously maintained, featuring a documented LN Engineering IMS bearing retrofit and a fresh rear main seal. The naturally aspirated 3.6L engine delivers linear power through a precise six-speed manual gearbox and a sophisticated all-wheel-drive system utilizing a viscous multi-plate clutch. The chassis remains taut with factory-spec Bilstein dampers and a reinforced subframe, while the braking system features ventilated cross-drilled rotors with four-piston monobloc calipers. The exterior retains its original factory paint depth with no evidence of oxidation, and the cabin shows zero bolster wear or UV degradation. A mechanically flawless, turn-key investment for the serious enthusiast.",
      "price": 48500.0,
